FBIS4-58828 "drnes089_j_94008" FBIS-NES-94-089 Daily Report 6 May 1994 ARABIAN PENINSULA Yemen YSP's Al-Bid Denies Attack on Dhamar Power Station YSP's Al-Bid Denies Attack on Dhamar Power Station EA0605192894 Aden Yemeni Republic Radio Network in English 1600 GMT 6 May 94 EA0605192894 Aden Yemeni Republic Radio Network English BFN [Text] Mr. 'Ali Salim al-Bid, secretary general of the Yemeni Socialist Party [YSP], has greeted the masses of the Yemeni people and their unitary armed forces. He affirmed in a statement to the Channel Two that the Yemeni people with vast experience of the unity and democracy. [sentence as heard] He affirmed that the unitary armed forces never attacked the power station in Dhamar and that the breakdown of the station was due to the shelling carried out by the central security forces in Dhamar. He affirmed that the economic installations belong to the whole Yemeni people and pointed out that all Yemenis are equal regardless of their birthplace. He called on the masses to join their hands with the armed forces to fight against those who seek to ignite war.
